OL,6,FLiverpool Crown Court was told the 54-
OL,7,Fyear-old was "in a rage" and his
OL,8,F"anger had completely taken hold of
OL,9,Fhim".
OL,11,FHe was "prepared to cause those in the
OL,12,Fcrowd, even children, serious harm if
OL,13,Fnecessary to achieve his aim of
OL,14,Fgetting through," prosecutor Paul
OL,15,FGreaney KC said.
OL,17,FDoyle previously pleaded guilty to 31
OL,18,Foffences relating to seriously
OL,19,Finjuring people during the victory
OL,20,Fparade on 26 May.
