OL,6,FDespite having cried throughout much
OL,7,Fof the hearing at Liverpool Crown
OL,8,FCourt, he was not in tears as Judge
OL,9,FMenary described his actions.
OL,11,FDoyle stared straight ahead, blinking,
OL,12,Fwith no expression as the judge
OL,13,Fsentenced him to 21 years and six
OL,14,Fmonths in prison. There was no
OL,15,Freaction from him as he was taken down
OL,16,Ffrom the dock.
OL,18,F"It is almost impossible to comprehend
OL,19,Fhow any right-thinking person could
OL,20,Fact as you did," Judge Menary said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/15
